You can load the file using the [`file` function][1] and then extract the list of accounts that you&#39;ll need by decoding the JSON with [`jsondecode`][2] and then selecting the `accounts` key.

As an example:

```hcl
locals {
  accounts = jsondecode(file(&quot;accounts.json&quot;)).accounts
}

output example {
  value = local.accounts
}
```

This will return the following:

```
example = [
  &quot;1234567890&quot;,
  &quot;0987654321&quot;,
  &quot;1029384756&quot;,
  &quot;6574839201&quot;,
  &quot;0192837465&quot;,
]
```

If you then wanted to put that into your policy you&#39;d want to use the [`formatlist` function][3] to pass a list of accounts into a single string format:

```hcl
output &quot;example&quot; {
  value = formatlist(&quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/%s/*&quot;, local.accounts)
}
```

This outputs:

```
example = [
  &quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/1234567890/*&quot;,
  &quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/0987654321/*&quot;,
  &quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/1029384756/*&quot;,
  &quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/6574839201/*&quot;,
  &quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/0192837465/*&quot;,
]
```

If you notice carefully though, Terraform uses trailing commas in lists which is invalid JSON so would create an invalid JSON structure for your IAM policy. To fix that we can then re-encode it into JSON with [`jsonencode`][4]:

```hcl
output &quot;example&quot; {
  value = jsonencode(formatlist(&quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/%s/*&quot;, local.accounts))
}
```

Which then outputs:

```
example = [&quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/1234567890/*&quot;,&quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/0987654321/*&quot;,&quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/1029384756/*&quot;,&quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/6574839201/*&quot;,&quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/0192837465/*&quot;]
```

without the trailing comma.

Putting this altogether you can then create your IAM policy like this:

```hcl
locals {
  accounts = jsondecode(file(&quot;accounts.json&quot;)).accounts
}

resource aws_iam_policy policy {
  name        = &quot;example&quot;
  path        = &quot;/&quot;

  policy = &lt;&lt;EOF
{
  &quot;Version&quot;: &quot;2012-10-17&quot;,
  &quot;Statement&quot;: [
    {
      &quot;Action&quot;: [
        &quot;s3:PutObject&quot;
      ],
      &quot;Effect&quot;: &quot;Allow&quot;,
      &quot;Resource&quot;: ${jsonencode(formatlist(&quot;arn:aws:s3:::bucket_name/AWSLogs/%s/*&quot;, local.accounts))}
    }
  ]
}
EOF
}
```

  [1]: https://www.terraform.io/docs/configuration/functions/file.html
  [2]: https://www.terraform.io/docs/configuration/functions/jsondecode.html
  [3]: https://www.terraform.io/docs/configuration/functions/formatlist.html
  [4]: https://www.terraform.io/docs/configuration/functions/jsonencode.html

